fly through one of the most scenic landscapes in the world.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5922029\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5922029\"><div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup CaptionedImage\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<img alt=\"Large bird with black body and a pink feather-less head perched on a white rock and looking at you.\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/grca-condor-08878_1.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;maxheight=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;format=webp\" title=\"Large bird with black body and a pink feather-less head perched on a white rock and looking at you.\"/>\n<figcaption>California condor. NPS/M.Quinn </figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5920748\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5920748\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Learn more: <a href=\"/articles/california-condor-recovery.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=5451249,california-condor-recovery.htm,30335|\">California Condor Reintroduction &amp; Recovery</a></h2>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5922031\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5922031\"><div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup CaptionedImage\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<img alt=\"Perched on rocks, two young birds have black feathers covering their bodies and heads. One is in profile and the second is facing forward.l\" src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/condor-chicks.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;maxheight=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;format=webp\" title=\"Perched on rocks, two young birds have black feathers covering their bodies and heads. One is in profile and the second is facing forward.l\"/>\n<figcaption>Two young California condors, some of the first to fledge in the wild, after condors were reintroduced into the Grand Canyon region in 1996. <p class=\"figcredit\">Photos circa 2004. Left: NPS/C.Olson, Right: NPS/M.Lellouch</p></figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5922033\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5922033\"><div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup CaptionedImage\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<img alt='Standing on a rock, with wings fully extended, a large black bird with a pink head. Attached to one wing is a tag that reads \"87.\"' src=\"/grca/learn/nature/images/grca-condor-wings.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;maxheight=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;format=webp\" title='Standing on a rock, with wings fully extended, a large black bird with a pink head. Attached to one wing is a tag that reads \"87.\"'/>\n<figcaption>California condor with wings fully extended. NPS/M.Quinn </figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5456097\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5456097\"></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5922036\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5922036\">\n\n<div class=\"container ListingList ListingResults\" id=\"searchListing-B954BC79-CC30-861D-D28B6C581EED6A32\">\n<h2>More Information About California Condors</h2>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"results\">\n<a name=\"results\"></a>\n<div class=\"display-list-view\" id=\"display-list-view\">\n<div class=\"info-micro-filter\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<div class=\"result-count\"></div>\n<div class=\"result-selectors\">\n<div class=\"result-facet-Parks_Item result-facet-select\" data-facetfield=\"Parks_Item\" data-facettitle=\"Location\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<form action=\"#\" class=\"micro-filter facet-parks\">\n<span class=\"visu